    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Pieter Nanninck to Miklós Oláh ([Leuven], 6 May [1538])</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Damião de Góis, who is handing over the letter, is not only of noble
                            birth but also has unparalleled erudition; if he has the chance, Oláh
                            should talk to him because Damião de Góis often says how much he desires
                            it.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Idem Nannius Domino Nicolao <del corresp="Olahus">Olacho</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Olaho</add> etc. </p>
                <p>Salutem plurimam. Qui tibi meas litteras praefert, <persName>Damianus a
                        Goes</persName>,<note type="critic">Damião de Góis, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Polet</hi> 1936, 264 and 273; and <hi rend="smallcap">Feist Hirsch</hi>
                        1967.</note> est eques Lusitanus non minus claritudine generis, quam
                    humanitate morum et litteris et litteratorum moribus insignis. Si patientur tuae
                    occupationes, velim, illum in colloquium admittes, senties illum morum
                    sinceritate, candore, fide, humanitate, modestia tibi simillimum. Saepius de te
                    mecum loquitur, tuae consuetudinis cupidissimus est. Bene vale, Optime Patrone. </p>
                <p>Pridiae Nonas Maias. Raptim.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
